   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>THE TRIUNE GOD'S REVELATION AND HIS MOVE MESSAGE FOUR THE WAY TO RECEIVE REVELATION FROM THE HOLY WORD AND SEE VISION THROUGH REVELATION Scripture Reading: Eph 6:17-18; 1:17-18; Acts 26:16-19; 16:9-10; 1:8; 10:17-20 OUTLINE The way to receive revelation from the holy Word: To read the holy Word and apprehend its contents in facts: To be familiar with the text.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>By the help of the original text Hebrew and Greek.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>By learning to know the types figures and shadows.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>To receive the divine revelation by exercising our spirit to contact the Lord through pray-reading Eph 6:17-18: Not by our natural understanding ability.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Not by our fanciful imaginations.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>But by the spirit of wisdom and revelation Eph 1:17.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Through much prayer in contacting the Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The way to see vision through the divine revelation: Through the enlightenment of the divine light Eph 1:18b.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>By contacting the Lord through the reviewing of the divine revelation in our spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>By having the spiritual sight Eph 1:18a.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The divine vision is mostly concerning God's move Acts 26:16-19; 16:9-10; 1:8; 10:17-20.</S>
   </TEXT>
